review_blob: Cask Conditioned. Amber coloured with a thin white head. Aroma is tart lemon, Tropical Fruit. Flavour is semi sweet, earthy honey, woody, spicy hop. Moderate carbonation, semi sweet. Nice dry bitter finish.
Cask 16/05/2015 pours Amber with a white foamy head. Sweet malty aroma. Tastes sweet with a slight bitter aftertaste. fruity, fruitcakeish (raisin) almost spicy.
Bottle 2014, 15/05/2015 dark Amber in colour. Sweet fruity aroma tastes treacle, sweet slightly raisin. Seasonable for 9%!
Bottle 15/05/2015 Lush copper colour with a foamy head. Aromas citrusy and spicy. Carbonation gives a strange sensation on the tongue. Slight bitterness with citrus topical flavours. Tasty!
Cask 15/05/2015. Clear golden colour, slight spicy, malty aroma and flavour. Really smooth and good mouthfeel but slightly bland

Bottle 15/05/2015. Pours almost like a rose wine, deep colour, sparkling with a white head. Small amount of sediment. Huge fruit aroma and flavour sweet, but tartness offsets this and keeps it from becoming too cloy.
beer_name: Celt Experience Goddess Of The Spring

review_blob: Cask 15/05/2015 golden in colour, no head. Citrus/fruity aroma. Bitter with a citrus finish
